      "comment": "GOOD HARMONY (8) presents third up here having finished sixth in both starts back from a short spell, solid at Sandown Hillside fresh and again at Bendigo. This looks relatively thin and she maps for every chance. CORVIGLIA (3) was just fair fresh at Ballarat but that was only his second career run having been close up on debut last time in. He can improve quickly. SONIC BELLE (9) hasn't troubled the scorers in two runs to date but was okay behind a dominant winner at Geelong and this looks easier from a soft draw. LUXOR GOLD (4) gets blinkers on to help with his manners and might be an improver while DUKE OF CLARENCE (1) was solid over this route last time and is in the mix.",
